ome%20down%2C%26quot%3B%20he%20wrote%2C%20%26quot%3Bmost%20of%20what%20I%20see%20in%20the%20future%20is%20inflationary%3A%20continued%20high%20fiscal%20deficits%2C%20the%20remilitarization%20of%20the%20world%20and%20the%20need%20for%20infrastructure%20investment%2C%20including%20the%20green%20economy%20and%20the%20restructuring%20of%20trade%20and%20tariffs.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EDimon%20said%20he%20expects%20rising%20costs%20to%20create%20a%20%26quot%3Btug-of-war%26quot%3B%20over%20the%20direction%20of%20interest%20rates%2C%20with%20long-term%20borrowing%20costs%20ultimately%20heading%20higher.%20%26quot%3BAll%20things%20being%20equal%2C%20the%20slower%20the%20growth%2C%20the%20lower%20the%20interest%20rates%2C%20and%20the%20higher%20the%20inflation%2C%20the%20higher%20the%20interest%20rates%2C%26quot%3B%20he%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EHe%20even%20referenced%20'%26quot%3Bstagflation%2C%26quot%3B%20a%20term%20popularized%20before%20the%20turn%20of%20the%20century%20to%20describe%20an%20unpleasant%20cocktail%20of%20high%20inflation%2C%20high%20unemployment%2C%20and%20tepid%20economic%20growth.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BThis%20tug-of-war%20can%20go%20on%20for%20some%20time%2C%20but%20it's%20good%20to%20remember%20that%20in%20the%20stagflation%20of%20the%201970s%2C%20recessions%20did%20not%20stop%20the%20inexorable%20trend%20of%20rising%20rates%2C%26quot%3B%20he%20wrote.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EDimon%20stopped%20short%20of%20saying%20the%20economy%20is%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fstock-market-crash-trump-tariffs-recession-doge-china-trade-war-2025-4%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Eheaded%20for%20a%20recession%3C%2Fa%3E.%20Following%20a%20two-day%20stock%20sell-off%20last%20week%2C%20the%20dreaded%20%26quot%3BR%26quot%3B%20word%20has%20been%20on%20everyone's%20lips.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EHe%20also%20suggested%20that%20stock%20market%20pain%20may%20not%20be%20over.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BNo%20matter%20how%20you%20measure%20it%2C%20equity%20va