add%20a%20volunteer%20section%20if%20it's%20relevant%20to%20what%20you%20want%20to%20do%2C%20but%20on%20its%20own%2C%20it's%20a%20waste%20of%20space.%20The%20same%20applies%20to%20awards.%20In%20the%20federal%20workforce%2C%20we%20have%20so%20many%20medals.%20People%20don't%20understand%20what%20those%20medals%20mean%20just%20by%20listing%20them.%20If%20you%20explain%20using%20metrics%20and%20something%20to%20quantify%20how%20you%20got%20that%20award%2C%20civilians%20will%20understand%20that%20better.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EOnly%20write%20a%20cover%20letter%20if%20it's%20required.%20If%20you're%20doing%20a%20career%20transition%2C%20that's%20when%20the%20cover%20letter%20comes%20in%20handy.%20The%20cover%20letter%20is%20just%20meant%20to%20explain%20any%20discrepancies%20in%20your%20r%C3%A9sum%C3%A9%20or%20reintroduce%20some%20ideas.%20It's%20not%20to%20regurgitate%20what's%20already%20in%20your%20r%C3%A9sum%C3%A9.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%20data-toc-id%3D%5C%227ff66d0b-8709-482b-8bf0-dce5933cf055%5C%22%3E3.%20Use%20corporate%20language%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EEvery%20person%20I%20work%20with%20has%20the%20skills.%20The%20problem%20is%20they%20don't%20know%20they%20have%20those%20skills%20or%20they%20don't%20know%20how%20to%20explain%20it%20in%20corporate%20language.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EOften%2C%20they%20just%20list%20their%20responsibilities.%20%26quot%3BI%20was%20responsible%20for%20managing%2010%20people.%26quot%3B%20You%20need%20to%20change%20that%20language%20to%20%26quot%3BI%20led%20and%20mentored%2010%20people%2C%26quot%3B%20in%20project%20management%20or%20whatever%20area%20it%20was.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EPeople%20don't%20know%20how%20to%20sell%20themselves%2C%20especially%20in%20the%20military%2C%20because%20we're%20so%20used%20to%20being%20in%20leadership%20roles%20and%20saying%20what%20our%20team%20did.%20We%20trained%20our%20team.%20We%20showed%20them%20how%20to%20do%20things%2C%20but%20sometimes%20we%20don't%20know%20how%20to%20take%20credit%20for%20things%20that%20we%20did.%20%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EMake%20sure%20you%20use%20action%20verbs%20and%20detail%20your%20accomplishments.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%20data-toc-id%3D%5C%22be3ca0dc-3bb0-44c1-8d6d-9590bb370009%5C%22%3E4.%20Include%20metrics%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EIn%20the%20federal%20government%20and%20in%20the%20military%2C%20you%20don't%20usually%20keep%20metrics%20because%20everything's%20funded%20by%20the%20government.%20But%20in%20the%20corporate%20world%2C%20companies%20want%20to%20know%20how%20much%20money%20you%20can%20make%20them%20and%20how%20much%20money%20you%20can%20save%20them.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThinking%20in%20those%20terms%20can%20be%20challenging%2C%20but%20many%20people%20in%20the%20federal%20workforce%20and%20military%20do%20work%20with%20budgets%2C%20especially%20those%20in%20more%20senior%20positions%20or%20those%20who%20work%20in%20logistics.%20They're%20ordering%20parts%20for%20tactical%20vehicles%20or%20aviation%20or%20they're%20managing%20budgets.%20They%20just%20don't%20know%20how%20to%20articulate%20that.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ESo%2C%20that's%20what%20I%20pull%20out%20of%20them.%20When%20they%20say%2C%20I%20managed%20million-dollar%20equipment%20I'm%20like%2C%20%26quot%3BDid%20you%20manage%20it%3F%20What%20else%20did%20you%20do%3F%20Did%20you%20order%20parts%3F%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cdiv%3ERead%20the%20original%20article%20on%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fresume-tips-for-federal-government-workers-transitioning-private-sector-2025-4%5C%22%3EBusiness%20Insider%3C%2Fa%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1744020121000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F67efe8ad5d203112923e18a3%3Fformat%3Djpeg%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fresume-tips-for-federal-government-workers-transitioning-private-sector-2025-4%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22Former%20federal%20workers%20can%20go%20anywhere%20with%20their%20skills%20%E2%80%94%20but%20they%20need%20to%20know%20how%20to%20explain%20it%20in%20a%20way%20that%20makes%20sense%20to%20civilians.%22%2C%22author%22%3A%22aaltchek%40insider.com%20(Ana%20Altchek)%22%2C%22engagement%22%3A35%2C%22canonicalUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fresume-tips-for-federal-government-workers-transitioning-private-sector-2025-4%22%2C%22cdnAmpUrl%22%3A%22%22%2C%22ampUrl%22%3A%22%22%7D%2C%7B%22title%22%3A%22Govt%20hikes%20excise%20duty%20on%20petrol%2C%20diesel%20by%20%E2%82%B92%2Fltr%3B%20retail%20prices%20unchanged%22%2C%22content%22%3A%22%22%2C%22published%22%3A1744020083000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.business-standard.com%2Findustry%2Fnews%2Fgovt-increases-excise-duty-on-petrol-diesel-by-2-per-litre-reports-125040700649_1.html%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22The%20excise%20duty%20on%20petrol%20was%20increased%20to%20Rs%2013%20per%20litre%20and%20that%20on%20diesel%20to%20Rs%2010%2C%20according%20to%20an%20official%20order%22%2C%22author%22%3A%22%22%2C%22engagement%22%3A0%2C%22canonicalUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.business-standard.com%2Findustry%2Fnews%2Fgovt-increases-excise-duty-on-petrol-diesel-by-2-per-litre-reports-125040700649_1.html%22%2C%22cdnAmpUrl%22%3A%22%22%2C%22ampUrl%22%3A%22%22%7D%2C%7B%22title%22%3A%22JLR%20reports%201.1%25%20sales%20growth%20in%20Q4%2C%20achieves%20net%20debt%20zero%20in%20FY25%22%2C%22content%22%3A%22%22%2C%22published%22%3A1744020003000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.business-standard.com%2Fcompanies%2Fnews%2Fjaguar-land-rover-jlr-q4-net-debt-zero-fy25-tata-motors-us-trump-tariffs-125040700645_1.html%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22The%20announcement%20comes%20soon%20after%20JLR%20announced%20a%20temporary%20pause%20in%20the%20shipments%20to%20the%20US%20in%20response%20to%20the%2025%20per%20cent%20tariff%20on%20auto%20imports%20imposed%20by%20the%20Donald%20Trump%20administration%22%2C%22author%22%3A%22%22%2C%22engagement%22%3A0%2C%22canonicalUrl%22%3A%22%22%2C%22cdnAmpUrl%22%3A%22%22%2C%22ampUrl%22%3A%22%22%7D%2C%7B%22title%22%3A%22Opinion%3A%20India%20Has%20A%20Rare%20Opportunity%20In%20Trump%20Tariffs%22%2C%22content%22%3A%22%3Cp%3EOn%20April%202%2C%20US%20President%20Donald%20Trump%20threw%20a%20gauntlet%20to%20the%20world%20and%20the%20post-1945%20US-constructed%20global%20order%20with%20across-the-board%20and%20significant%20country-specific%20tariffs.%20The%20tariff%20rates%20were%20higher%20than%20what%20was%20anticipated%20even%20by%20Trump's%20key%20business%20supporters%20in%20the%20US.%20Markets%20reacted%20negatively%20worldwide%2C%20falling%2010%25%20in%20America.%20The%20US%20Federal%20Reserve%20is%20now%20expected%20to%20hold%20back%20on%20any%20interest%20rate%20cuts%2C%20anticipating%20an%20inflationary%20impact.%20Analytical%20comments%20are%20comparing%20the%20disruption%20to%2C%20potentially%2C%20the%20Great%20Depression%20of%20the%201930s.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EWhile%20there%20is%20global%20anger%20and%20anxiety%2C%20most%20countries%20have%20so%20far%20refrained%20from%20retaliatory%20action%2C%20though%20they%20have%20asserted%20their%20right%20to%20do%20so.%20China%2C%20however%2C%20is%20among%20the%20few%20that%20have%20already%20declared%20matching%20reciprocal%20tariffs%20of%2034%25%20on%20imports%20from%20the%20US.%20Only%2C%20it%20exports%20far%20more%20than%20it%20imports.%20Beijing's%20aim%20is%20more%20to%20impose%20political%20pain%20on%20Trump%20by%20cutting%20back%20supplies%20from%20his%20supporters%2C%20particularly%20in%20the%20US%20agriculture%20belt.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Ch2%3E%3Cstrong%3EA%20Divided%20World%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fh2%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EVoices%20in%20the%20European%20Union%20are%20divided%2C%20with%20the%20European%20Commission%20articulating%20the%20need%20for%20retaliation%2C%20though%20many%20leading%20countries%2C%20including%20Germany%20and%20France%2C%20are%20currently%20undergoing%20their%20own%20political%20instability%20and%20transition.%20They%20have%20thus%20preferred%20a%20cautious%20approach%20and%20negotiations%20to%20bring%20down%20the%20rates%20rather%20than%20getting%20into%20competitive%20escalation.%20Canada%20and%20Mexico%2C%20already%20targets%20of%20specific%20tariffs%20on%20steel%20and%20aluminum%20imports%2C%20were%20spared%20the%20April%202%20across-the-board%2010%25%20tariffs.%20No%20doubt%2C%20these%20were%20on%20account%20of%20enforcement%20difficulties%20that%20would%20arise%20given%20the%20deep%20supply%20chain%20integration%20under%20the%20US-Mexico-Canada%20Agreement%20(USMCA)%20finalised%20in%20Trump's%20first%20term.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20Prime%20Minister%20of%20Singapore%2C%20meanwhile%2C%20in%20an%20address%20to%20his%20country%2C%20declared%20the%20current%20global%20order%20dead%20and%20warned%20of%20the%20need%20to%20prepare%20for%20adjustments.%20He%20said%20smaller%20countries%20would%20be%20left%20with%20little%20bargaining%20power%20if%2C%20in%20the%20next%20phase%2C%20trade%20agreements%20are%20negotiated%20bilaterally%20rather%20than%20through%20multilaterally%20agreed%20rules%20and%20norms.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Ch2%3E%3Cstrong%3EGrowing%20Republican%20Control%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fh2%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThere%20are%20many%20lessons%20that%20other%20countries%20will%20need%20to%20draw%20as%20the%20US%20veers%20away%20from%20globalisation%20of%20trade%20and%20production%2C%20precipitated%20by%20imbalances%20flowing%20from%20China's%20misuse%20of%20WTO%20(World%20Trade%20Organization)%20provisions%2C%20which%20has%20concentrated%20as%20much%20as%2032%25%20of%20global%20manufacturing%20in%20the%20country%20through%20subsidies%20and%20forced%20technology%20transfers.%20We%20should%20expect%20continued%20policy%20unpredictability%20from%20the%20US%20as%20the%20impact%20of%20its%20measures%20is%20assessed%20for%20domestic%20political%20and%20economic%20gain.%20There%20are%20divisions%20among%20parties%20and%20businesses%20about%20the%20right%20approach%2C%20and%20deep%20polarisation%20in%20US%20society.%20Already%2C%20protests%20against%20government%20policies%20have%20begun.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ENonetheless%2C%20Trump's%20core%20base%20remains%20with%20him%2C%20due%20to%20which%20Republicans%20have%20not%20yet%20come%20out%20in%20any%20effective%20or%20large-scale%20opposition.%20Also%2C%20with%20Republicans%20in%20control%20of%20both%20houses%20of%20the%20US%20Congress%2C%20the%20system%20of%20checks%20and%20balances%20envisaged%20in%20the%20US%20Constitution%20is%20not%20entirely%20in%20place%20at%20present.%20Courts%20and%20their%20decisions%20are%20being%20politically%20challenged%20through%20non-cooperation%20or%20threats%20of%20impeachment.%20Persons%20with%20radical%20right-wing%20views%20are%20seen%20as%20having%20outsized%20influence%20on%20personnel%20and%20policy%20decisions%2C%20with%20one%20such%20figure%2C%20Laura%20Loomer%2C%20seen%20as%20being%20responsible%20for%20the%20recent%20firing%20of%20several%20National%20Security%20Council%20officials%2C%20as%20well%20as%20of%20Timothy%20Hugh%2C%20the%20Director-General%20of%20the%20US%20National%20Security%20Agency.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Ch2%3E%3Cstrong%3EThe%20February%20Meeting%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fh2%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EIndia%2C%20no%20doubt%2C%20has%20to%20weigh%20its%20own%20response%20carefully.%20The%20US%20is%20its%20largest%20trading%20partner%20at%20%24200%20billion%2C%20with%20a%20%2445%20billion%20surplus%20being%20in%20India's%20favor.%20In%20the%20past%2C%20several%20countries%2C%20including%20China%2C%20the%20Republic%20of%20Korea%2C%20Japan%2C%20and%20many%20in%20Europe%2C%20grew%20due%20to%20substantial%20access%20to%20the%20US%20market.%20The%20same%20opportunity%20will%20not%20be%20available%20for%20some%20time%20now%2C%20given%20the%20current%20political%20climate%20in%20the%20US%20around%20trade%20and%20distribution%20of%20production.%20It%20would%20be%20important%20to%20work%20out%20a%20bilateral%2C%20multi-sectoral%20free%20trade%20agreement%20to%20get%20around%20the%20new%20US%20tariffs%20and%20gain%20market%20access%20beyond%20competitors.%20The%2054%25%20overall%20tariffs%20on%20China%20and%2046%25%20on%20Vietnam%20suggest%20possibilities%20for%20competitive%20advantage%2C%20against%20the%2026%25%20tariffs%20Indian%20products%20face.%20Following%20the%20Indian%20Prime%20Minister's%20meeting%20with%20Trump%20in%20Washington%20DC%20on%20February%2013%2C%20both%20countries%20announced%20an%20agreement%20to%20work%20towards%20a%20trade%20agreement%20and%20complete%20its%20first%20tranche%20by%20the%20fall%20of%20this%20year.%20Negotiations%20have%20commenced%2C%20with%20a%20visit%20of%20the%20Indian%20Commerce%20Minister%20to%20the%20US%2C%20and%2C%20subsequently%2C%20of%20an%20Assistant%20US%20Trade%20Representative%20to%20India.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EAccording%20to%20reports%2C%20following%20a%20broad%20understanding%20on%20the%20approach%20to%20be%20taken%2C%20the%20two%20sides%20will%20now%20get%20down%20to%20detailed%2C%20sector-specific%20discussions.%20If%20a%20first%20tranche%20is%20indeed%20successfully%20concluded%2C%20we%20can%20expect%20a%20Trump%20visit%20to%20India%20later%20this%20year%20for%20a%20Quad%20Summit.%20In%20that%20case%2C%20there%20will%20be%20pressure%20on%20both%20systems%20to%20generate%20more%20positive%20opportunities%20for%20cooperation.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Ch2%3E%3Cstrong%3ERoom%20To%20Wiggle%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fh2%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EIn%20January%202023%2C%20in%20the%20Biden%20era%2C%20the%20US%20and%20India%20had%20launched%20a%20major%20new%20Initiative%20on%20Critical%20and%20Emerging%20Technologies%20(iCET)%2C%20seeking%20to%20deepen%20cooperation%20in%20AI%2C%20quantum%20technology%2C%20cyberspace%2C%206G%2C%20biotechnology%2C%20semiconductors%2C%20defence%20and%20space.%20The%20aim%20was%20to%20work%20on%20co-development%20of%20technologies%2C%20leading%20to%20production-sharing%20and%2C%20subsequently%2C%20sectoral%20trading%20facilitation.%20The%20semiconductor%20space%20saw%20some%20progress%20with%20the%20announcement%20of%20new%20US%20investments%20in%20India%2C%20while%20in%20defence%2C%20things%20moved%20forward%20with%20the%20launch%20of%20INDUS-X%20(India-US%20Defense%20Acceleration%20Ecosystem).%20In%20the%20space%20sector%2C%20a%20decision%20was%20taken%2C%20inter%20alia%2C%20to%20launch%20a%20joint%20mission%20to%20the%20International%20Space%20Station.%20The%20current%20Trump%20administration%2C%20while%20walking%20away%20from%20many%20Biden-era%20initiatives%2C%20has%2C%20notably%2C%20kept%20the%20essence%20of%20iCET%2C%20though%20with%20a%20rebranded%20name%3A%20%E2%80%98TRUST'%2C%20which%20stands%20for%20Transforming%20the%20Relationship%20Using%20Strategic%20Technologies.%20This%20means%20there%20is%20potential%20for%20continued%20deepening%20of%20technology%20partnerships%20to%20mutual%20advantage%20and%20creating%20new%20opportunities%20for%20promoting%20sector-focused%20trade.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EDespite%20the%20tremendous%20disruption%20being%20caused%20by%20the%20latest%20US%20tariffs%20and%20trade%20policies%2C%20America%20will%20want%20to%20retain%20its%20status%20as%20the%20leading%20global%20economic%20and%20technology%20player.%20While%20it%20has%20taken%20measures%20against%20countries%20across%20the%20board%2C%20including%20its%20key%20allies%20and%20partners%2C%20such%20as%20Japan%20and%20various%20European%20countries%2C%20it%20has%20identified%20China%20as%20its%20main%20economic%2C%20technological%20and%20military%20challenge%20globally%2C%20one%20with%20the%20intent%20and%20capability%20to%20replace%20the%20US%20in%20the%20international%20system.%20US%20policymakers%20and%20businesses%20recognise%20that%20they%20need%20a%20partnership%20with%20India's%201.4%20billion%20people%20as%20well%20as%20with%20its%20tech-human%20capital%20to%20take%20on%20the%20China%20challenge.%20Therein%20will%20lie%20the%20opportunity%20for%20India%2C%20despite%20all%20the%20uncertainty%20and%20upheaval%20currently.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cem%3E(The%20author%20is%20a%20former%20Indian%20ambassador%20to%20the%20US%2C%20France%20and%20Israel)%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3EDisclaimer%3A%20Th