%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Eshrinking%20number%20of%20openings%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20candidates%20could%20secure%20a%20coveted%20offer%20%E2%80%94%20only%20to%20experience%20a%20bait-and-switch%20of%20sorts.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EStefan%20Mai%2C%20cofounder%20of%20interview-prep%20startup%20Hello%20Interview%20and%20former%20senior%20engineering%20manager%20at%20Meta%2C%20told%20Business%20Insider%20that%20some%20job%20seekers%20finally%20snag%20senior%20positions%2C%20only%20for%20hiring%20managers%20to%20retract%20their%20original%20offers.%20An%20offer%20for%20a%20lower-level%20role%20is%20extended%20instead.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ESay%20hello%20to%20%26quot%3Bdownleveling.%26quot%3B%20Mai%20wrote%20extensively%20about%20the%20practice%20in%20a%20post%20for%20%26quot%3B%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fnewsletter.pragmaticengineer.com%2Fp%2Fthe-reality-of-tech-interviews%3Futm_campaign%3Demail-half-post%26r%3D1n9jf7%26utm_source%3Dsubstack%26utm_medium%3Demail%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EThe%20Pragmatic%20Engineer%3C%2Fa%3E.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BHiring%20managers%20and%20companies%20that%20are%20kind%20of%20looking%20at%20candidates%20are%20usually%20making%20this%20risk%20determination%2C%26quot%3B%20Mai%20told%20BI.%20%26quot%3BIt's%20kind%20of%20like%2C%20'Okay%2C%20we%20don't%20have%20all%20of%20the%20evidence%20this%20person%20can%20be%20successful%20at%20this%20level.%20You%20know%20what%3F%20What%20if%20we%20extend%20them%20an%20offer%20at%20a%20level%20that%20we%20have%20more%20evidence%20for%3F'%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ELeveling%20itself%20is%20standard%20practice%20in%20engineering%20interviews%2C%20Mai%20said.%20It%20only%20means%20the%20interviewer%20will%20be%20measuring%20the%20candidate's%20competency%20against%20a%20certain%20bar%20%E2%80%94%20from%20more%20junior%20tiers%20such%20as%20L1%2FL2%20all%20the%20way%20up%20to%20highly%20desirable%20senior%20L6%20or%20L7%20roles.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BLeveling%20for%20software%20engineers%20is%20basically%20where%20you%20have%20a%20numeric%20value%20that's%20defined%20mostly%20by%20seniority%2C%20and%20it%20comes%20with%20different%20responsibilities%20at%20each%20higher%20level%2C%26quot%3B%20he%20said.%20%26quot%3BWhen%20you%20interview%20with%20a%20company%2C%20usually%20you're%20interviewing%20for%20a%20specific%20level.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EDownleveling%2C%20Mai%20said%2C%20occurs%20when%20a%20company%20determines%20they%20still%20want%20to%20onboard%20a%20candidate%20%E2%80%94%20just%20not%20for%20the%20role%20they%20were%20originally%20interviewed%20to%20fill.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThough%20the%20concept%20of%20downleveling%20isn't%20new%2C%20according%20to%20Mai%2C%20the%20fiercely%20competitive%20market%20has%20become%20more%20conducive%20to%20the%20practice.%20With%20more%20candidates%20than%20ever%20to%20choose%20from%2C%20companies%20are%20less%20willing%20to%20roll%20the%20dice%20on%20someone%20who%20%3Cem%3Ealmost%20%3C%2Fem%3Emeets%20their%20list%20of%20requirements%2C%20rather%20than%20checking%20every%20box.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BI%20think%20recently%2C%20the%20hiring%20market%20has%20become%20such%20that%20they've%20got%20lots%20more%20candidates%20coming%20through%2C%20so%20their%20appetite%20for%20taking%20on%20that%20risk%20is%20diminished%2C%26quot%3B%20he%20said.%20%26quot%3BNow%2C%20there's%20generally%20enough%20candidates%20in%20the%20pipeline%2C%20especially%20for%20the%20bigger%20companies.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAnd%20if%20a%20candidate%20does%20reject%20a%20downleveled%20offer%2C%20he%20added%2C%20hiring%20managers%20are%20unlikely%20to%20have%20to%20wait%20long%20for%20someone%20else%20to%20jump%20at%20the%20chance.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EMai%20went%20on%20to%20describe%20an%20experience%20working%20with%20a%20client%20who%20was%20chasing%20a%20senior%20position%20at%20Meta.%20He%20said%20the%20candidate%20cleared%20the%20interview%20process%20for%20their%20ideal%2C%20senior-level%20role%2C%20but%20they%20were%20later%20offered%20a%20midlevel%20position.%20Mai%20said%20the%20company%20cited%20a%20new%20policy%20that%20required%20six%20years%20of%20experience%20for%20advanced%20positions.%20Having%20no%20better%20options%2C%20Maid%20said%20the%20candidate%20chose%20to%20accept.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BThat's%20unheard%20of%20to%20me.%20I%20think%2C%20you%20know%2C%20if%20I%20was%20actually%20still%20a%20hiring%20manager%20at%20Meta%2C%20I%20would%20have%20been%20making%20a%20huge%20ruckus%20out%20of%20this%2C%20because%20I%20think%20that's%20deeply%20unfair%20to%20the%20candidate%2C%20and%20it%20reflects%20poorly%20on%20the%20company%2C%26quot%3B%20he%20said.%20%26quot%3BTo%20be%20honest%2C%20I%20think%20that%20they%20basically%20went%20back%20on%20what%20they%20had%20said.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EMeta%20didn't%20immediately%20respond%20to%20a%20request%20for%20comment%20by%20Business%20Insider.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ESo%2C%20is%20it%20ever%20a%20good%20idea%20to%20take%20a%20downleveled%20offer%3F%20For%20those%20hungry%20to%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fnvidia-leader-advice-young-software-engineers-programmers-writing-math-skills-2025-3%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Ebreak%20into%20big-name%20tech%3C%2Fa%3E%20companies%2C%20Mai%20said%20it%20might%20be.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BIt%20really%20depends%20on%20the%20individual.%20So%2C%20for%20a%20bunch%20of%20candidates%2C%20getting%20your%20foot%20in%20at%20the%20door%20at%20like%2C%20a%20big%20company%20like%20Google%20or%20Meta%20means%20that%2C%20in%20subsequent%20job%20changes%2C%20you're%20going%20to%20have%20a%20much%20easier%20time%2C%26quot%3B%20he%20said.%20%26quot%3BThere's%20kind%20of%20this%20breaking%20into%20Big%20Tech%20that%20I%20think%20people%20are%20very%20familiar%20with.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EDespite%20the%20temptation%20to%20take%20the%20news%20personally%2C%20Mai%20encourages%20candidates%20to%20remain%20cool-headed%20and%20reflect%20on%20whether%20their%20new%20offer%20might%20still%20benefit%20their%20careers.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BIn%20a%20lot%20of%20cases%2C%20that's%20kind%20of%20generally%20our%20advice.%20When%20candidates%20have%20this%20happen%20to%20them%2C%20we%20ask%20them%20to%20look%20objectively%20at%20what%20they're%20being%20offered%2C%20and%20not%20the%20emotional%20kind%20of%20response%20of%2C%20'Hey%2C%20I%20got%20something%20lower%20than%20I%20was%20expecting%2C'%26quot%3B%20he%20said.%20%26quot%3BThose%20expectations%20aren't%20all%20that%20helpful.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThat%20being%20said%20%E2%80%94%20if%20you've%20already%20got%20a%20seat%20at%20the%20table%2C%20you%20might%20be%20better%20positioned%20to%20be%20pickier.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BSay%20you're%20already%20in%20Big%20Tech%2C%26quot%3B%20Mai%20said.%20%26quot%3BAccepting%20that%20downlevel%20might%20actually%20be%20a%20bad%20move.%20It%20could%20be%20pulling%20you%20back%20in%20your%20career.%20It%20might%20mean%20several%20years%20before%20you%20get%20to%20the%20correct%20level.%20There's%20kind%20of%20a%20bunch%20of%20different%20considerations.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThat%20job%20seekers%20are%20facing%20decisions%20like%20these%2C%20though%2C%20betrays%20a%20brutal%20reality%20of%20the%20hiring%20market%20for%20software%20developers.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BI%20think%20people%20are%20more%20desperate%20now%2C%20and%20so%20they're%20willing%20to%20accept%20these%20lower%20offers%2C%26quot%3B%20Mai%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cdiv%3ERead%20the%20original%20article%20on%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fdownleveled-tech-coding-job-offers-on-rise-former-meta-manager-2025-4%5C%22%3EBusiness%20Insider%3C%2Fa%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1744018141000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F67eebfb363d72727e1991cc4%3Fformat%3Djpeg%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fdownleveled-tech-coding-job-offers-on-rise-former-meta-manager-2025-4%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22Stefan%20Mai%2C